thread.title: WU soccer plays to 1-1 tie with Northwest Missouri
thread.title_full: WU soccer plays to 1-1 tie with Northwest Missouri

author: Rick Peterson Jr.
title: WU soccer plays to 1-1 tie with Northwest Missouri
text:
WU soccer plays to 1-1 tie with Northwest Missouri Stauffer nets lone goal for the Ichabods Posted: October 11, 2015 - 5:15pm By Rick Peterson Jr. richard.peterson@cjonline.com 
Washburn came out for overtime against Northwest Missouri with a strong push, nearly ending the game after a cross for Bailey Wobig was caught by the Northwest goalkeeper at the last second. 
But that missed opportunity summed up the day for the Ichabods, who settled for a 1-1 tie with the Bearcats on Sunday at Yager Stadium. 
“Honestly, I thought Bailey was going to score on a header,” Washburn coach Chris Jones said. “We had some great chances the first five minutes of the overtime. 
“We allowed them to settle into their game and play the long ball and get us off balanced a little bit, which was unfortunate. But I thought we had some great chances in the second overtime.” 
Washburn (3-6-3, 2-3-1 MIAA) led 1-0 at halftime after Emily Stauffer scored on a penalty kick at the 19:30 mark. 
WU goalkeeper Kaitlin Minnich helped preserve the lead in the first half, recording four saves. Minnich kicked away a golden opportunity on a breakaway attempt for the Bearcats in the first half. 
“She was super big for us,” Jones said. “She saved us a couple times, for sure on that one-on-one situation.” 
Northwest evened the score after Anna Holden put a foot on a loose ball at the 55:18 mark after a free kick was sent in from about 50 yards out. 
Washburn put up 20 shots and had nine shots on goal while Northwest had 14 shots with six on goal. 
“We hit the post a couple times, and the keeper (Elizabeth Lee) made some tough saves,” Jones said. “Overall, I was pretty happy with the result. I’m not happy we tied; I thought we could have won the game. But that’s just how soccer goes.” 
The Ichabods finished the weekend 1-0-1, picking up a 1-0 win over Missouri Western on Friday night. 
“It’s the first time in a long time we’ve gone undefeated for a whole weekend,” Jones said. “We kind of feel good about that and will take the positive away from that. We didn’t play, necessarily, the greatest, but we didn’t play that bad. There’s a lot of positives to be taken away from today. We just have to keep building and keep getting better.” 
Washburn will begin a five-game road swing at Missouri Southern on Thursday. 
WASHBURN 1, NORTHWEST MISSOURI 1, 2 OT 
Northwest Missouri 0 1 0 0 – 1 
Washburn 1 0 0 0 – 1 
Northwest Missouri – Goal: Holden. 
Records – Northwest Missouri: 2-6-3, 1-4-1 MIAA; Washburn 3-6-3, 2-3-1.
